<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1873-11-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1873-11-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="605" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                            <head>No. 603.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to General <persName type="to">Sickles</persName>.</hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1873-11-14"><hi rend="italic">November</hi> 14,
                                        1873</date>.</dateline>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 406.]</seg></opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose herewith a copy of a
                                telegram sent to you this day, relating to the capture of the
                                Virginius, and also of the correspondence upon the same subject
                                which has taken place between the consul-general of the United
                                States at Havana and the captain-general of Cuba.</p>
                            <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                            <closer><signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>